;;;; autolisp-test/harness/inventory.sexp
;;;;
;;;; Inventory of every AutoLISP / Visual LISP entry defined in the local
;;;; specification draft, with an initial conformance classification.
;;;;
;;;; This file is intentionally restricted to the spec. Operators that
;;;; clautolisp installs as extensions (the longer Cxxr / Cxxxxr family,
;;;; ERROR, LCM, LOGXOR, VL-CATCH-ALL-ERROR-STACK) are documented in
;;;; clautolisp/autolisp-builtins-core/README.org under "clautolisp-
;;;; Specific Operators" rather than added here, so a conformance run
;;;; never confuses an implementation choice with a normative test.
;;;;
;;;; Each record is a property list. Field reading is portable between
;;;; AutoLISP and Common Lisp because it only relies on uppercase symbols,
;;;; strings, and proper lists. The file is loadable as a single readable
;;;; s-expression: (INVENTORY ...).
;;;;
;;;; Field semantics:
;;;;   KIND               - one of FUNCTION SPECIAL-FORM VARIABLE TYPE
;;;;                        READER-SYNTAX DISTINGUISHED-OBJECT CONDITION
;;;;   NAME               - the operator/entity name as it appears in the
;;;;                        specification, preserving case
;;;;   PROFILE            - one of STRICT AUTOCAD BRICSCAD
;;;;                        STRICT  : behaviour intended to hold on
;;;;                                  AutoCAD AND BricsCAD
;;;;                        AUTOCAD : behaviour attested or documented on
;;;;                                  AutoCAD only
;;;;                        BRICSCAD: behaviour attested or documented on
;;;;                                  BricsCAD only
;;;;   PLATFORM-TAGS      - subset of (WINDOWS LINUX MACOS); empty list
;;;;                        means platform-agnostic
;;;;   RUNTIME-TAGS       - subset of (COM VLA VLAX VLAX-CURVE VLR
;;;;                                   ARX BRX OBJECTDBX DCL GRAPHICS
;;;;                                   USER-INPUT EXPRESS-TOOLS DOSLIB)
;;;;                        empty list means no specific runtime extension
;;;;                        is required
;;;;   AUTHORITY          - one of DOCUMENTED TESTED-AUTOCAD TESTED-BRICSCAD
;;;;                        TESTED-BOTH INFERRED
;;;;                        Initial value DOCUMENTED keeps an explicit
;;;;                        reminder that vendor documentation may diverge
;;;;                        from actual product behaviour and that probes
;;;;                        are required to upgrade an entry to TESTED-*.
;;;;   SOURCE-EVIDENCE    - source path supporting the entry
;;;;
;;;; Initial classification rules (to be refined as probes accumulate):
;;;;   - PROFILE defaults to STRICT (maximal strict standard).
;;;;   - VLAX-* (excluding VLAX-CURVE-*) and VLA-* are tagged
;;;;     (COM ...) and require WINDOWS.
;;;;   - VLAX-CURVE-* are language-level helpers, no platform constraint.
;;;;   - VLR-* (reactors) are not Windows-bound.
;;;;   - DOS_* (DOSLib) are tagged DOSLIB and require WINDOWS.
;;;;   - ACET-* / ACET::* are tagged EXPRESS-TOOLS.
;;;;   - Entity, table, dictionary, layer-state, NENTSEL, REGAPP, XDROOM,
;;;;     XDSIZE entries are tagged OBJECTDBX. VLE-ENT*, VLE-TBL*, VLE-DICT*
;;;;     refinements are deliberately deferred to a later pass.
;;;;   - Graphics primitives (GR*) and screen-state functions are tagged
;;;;     GRAPHICS.
;;;;   - DCL functions (LOAD_DIALOG, *_TILE, *_LIST, *_IMAGE, etc.) are
;;;;     tagged DCL.
;;;;   - Interactive prompts (GETPOINT, GETSTRING, INITGET, ALERT, PROMPT,
;;;;     ...) are tagged USER-INPUT.
;;;;   - ARX-related entries are tagged ARX. BRX classification is reserved
;;;;     for entries surfaced by BricsCAD-specific probes.
;;;;
;;;; This file is generated by the inventory-extraction tooling under
;;;; autolisp-test/harness/. Manual edits to refine classification are
;;;; expected as conformance probes from real AutoCAD and BricsCAD runs
;;;; accumulate.
;;;;
;;;; Counts at generation time:
;;;;   FUNCTION             :  938
;;;;   SPECIAL-FORM         :   19
;;;;   VARIABLE             :    5
;;;;   TYPE                 :    5
;;;;   READER-SYNTAX        :    7
;;;;   DISTINGUISHED-OBJECT :    1
;;;;   CONDITION            :    1
;;;;   TOTAL                :  976
;;;;

(INVENTORY
(KIND READER-SYNTAX NAME "Integer Literal" PROFILE STRICT PLATFORM-TAGS () RUNTIME-TAGS () AUTHORITY DOCUMENTED SOURCE-EVIDENCE "autolisp-spec/documentation/autolisp-visual-lisp-specification-draft.org")
(KIND READER-SYNTAX NAME "Real Literal" PROFILE STRICT PLATFORM-TAGS () RUNTIME-TAGS () AUTHORITY DOCUMENTED SOURCE-EVIDENCE "autolisp-spec/documentation/autolisp-visual-lisp-specification-draft.org")
